This paper is likely to belong to the Electronic Design Automation (EDA) sub-category (cs.ET) as it proposes a high performance layout decomposer for triple patterning lithography (TPL), which is a critical step in the EDA process. The paper also mentions the use of semi-definite programming (SDP) and graph simplification, which are common techniques in EDA. 

The paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it discusses the use of density-based mapping and graph simplification, which are both related to data structures and algorithms. 

Computer Vision (cs.CV) is another possible sub-category as TPL is a technique used in the manufacturing of integrated circuits, which are used in many computer vision applications. 

The paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AR) sub-category as it uses SDP, which is a technique commonly used in optimization problems in AI. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a method for density balancing, which is a common problem in machine learning.
